text.tspan: So... been thinking about this UI and how to create an
emotional affect on the viewer from the score results.
The US department of homeland security uses a colour coding
system to identify the threat levels of “people of interest”.
Since we are just focusing the project on “trustworthiness”
now as the parameter, what do you guys think of incorporating
something like this into the algorithm’s score results?
We could then provide an additional layer of threat from the
AI, some kind of recommended course of action for authority
to take dependent on the threat level...
What do you guys think of this? It definitely changes
the narrative of the project... too far off track?
have I watched too many black mirror episodes? Better
to stick to a “trustworthiness” outcome rather than
turn the dial up into suspicion and danger?
